thread.title: Tough Start for Housing

author: Justin Lahart
title: Tough Start for Housing
text:
The housing market is slowing, and pressures will only build as the year goes on.
Sales of previously owned, or existing, homes slumped last month. The National Association of Realtors reported on Wednesday that existing home sales in January fell 3.2% from December, versus the gain economists expected to see. Sales were 4.8% below their year-earlier level, marking the biggest annual decline since August 2014.
